social_posts.post_text:
If I’m being honest I was very hesitant to post this. Why? You may ask. It’s easier for me to hide my pain than put it out there for people to see. I’m very protective over my children and the last thing I ever want is for my son to be the topic of conversation. You know how gossip works… people find joy in others’ pain. I don’t want that at the expense of my son. But in my heart I know what God wants from me. He wants me to put my pride to the side and humble myself and share my situation. I hope by doing this it could help others who are experiencing this. I don’t want people coming to my page and thinking wow her life is so perfect. I want you to know that every single human in this world has hurt and pain. Don’t let peoples’ page fool you. I’ve opened up about Eli’s speech delay in the past and then I stopped talking about it. I’m ready to talk about it again. Eli is almost 3 and is still not talking. As mothers we are united in our children’s suffering. When they hurt, we hurt. It pierces me watching my son cry in frustration because he can’t express himself to me. I’ve cried endless nights to God. I’ve traveled the world seeking holy sites to heal my son. In the midst of this I hear nothing from God. But I know in His silence He is working. He will not forsake me or my family. I know that Eli will have a beautiful testimony one day. To the parents who have children with developmental delay, autism, disabilities, or other health issues my heart is with you. 

.
.
.
.
.
.

MY HOME BIRTH 🏠🤍

God blessed me with one of the most profound experiences of my life. While feeling every single wave take over my entire being, I allowed my body to do that for which it was made: bring life into this world. The opportunity to unite my suffering with Christ’s and offer up the pain was something that I will cherish forever.  I had moments of fear and doubt. I questioned myself and felt like I was ready to give up. In those moments, I called out to Jesus and Mother Mary. They showed up, like they always do, and accompanied me every step of the way. You truly don’t know what you are capable of until God takes over and gives you the strength to do the impossible. I completed this birthing journey; my body was made to do this. 

A woman giving birth to a child has pain because her time has come; but when her baby is born she forgets the anguish because of her joy that a child is born into the world (John 16:21) 

#homebirth #naturalbirth #waterbirth #birthvideo #unmedicatedbirth #catholicmom #christianmom

Ave’s first daddy daughter dance 🤍

The bond between a father and daughter is so special. The first man she will fall in love with. It made me so emotional watching my baby girl get so excited. Ave kept saying, “Daddy is my Prince Charming.” She totally has stole my husband from me. I am okay with it…kinda haha.  I couldn’t help but flash back to my first daddy daughter dance with my father. Life is a dream and in the blink of an eye my baby has become a big girl.

Dubai itinerary below ⬇️

Day 1- The Burj Khalifa and The Dubai Mall. Make sure to catch the fountain show. It’s runs every 30 minutes starting at 6pm. You can also find the Dubai Aquarium & underwater zoo inside of the Dubai Mall. 
Day 2- Beach day: Aura Sky Pool and Dior pop up beach at Nammos. Enjoy night life at Mood Rooftop Lounge.
Day 3- Dubai Miracle Garden. Global Village during the night. Global Village is opened from October until April.
Day 4- Desert Safari Tour. This includes a dune buggy or quad bike and camel ride. 
Day 5- Head to Abu Dhabi for a day trip. Visit the Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque and the Qasr Al Watan Palace.

Make sure to save for your future trip to the UAE 🇦🇪
